<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-497] Snapshot tools may fail when #targets &gt; MaxStartups in sshd_config</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-497</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using ssh as the remote shell for zfs-based lustre snapshots, servers with large numbers of targets may fail to create snapshots on all relevant zfs datasets. A new ssh connection is attempted for each target, and when the total reaches the default&#160;maximum number of concurrent unauthenticated connections (10), there is a chance the next connection will be killed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; The solution suggested for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9368&quot; title=&quot;snapshot testing: ssh_exchange_identification: Connection closed by remote host&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9368&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9368&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; works for me: make sure that the MaxStartups value in /etc/ssh/sshd_config is at larger than the number of targets on the server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can a note about this appear in the documentation or man pages? It took me an embarrassingly long time to track it down.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre 2.12.7, CentOS 7.9, zfs 0.8.5</environment>
        <key id="66967">LUDOC-497</key>
